cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.CV, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a new survival analysis framework using deep learning and active learning with a novel sampling strategy. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with clinical data, which suggests that it could belong to the Clinical and Health Informatics (cs.CE) sub-category. The paper uses deep learning for feature representation, which suggests that it could belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper introduces a treatment recommendation approach, which suggests that it could belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
